<subSubSection id="C359657BFFA48272FF0DF8475D5DD7A2" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="414" pageId="4" pageNumber="413" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F0FFA48272FF0DF8475D5DD7A2" blockId="4.[151,1436,1951,2013]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="414" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA48273FF0DF8475962D0CE" bold="true" box="[151,273,1951,1976]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pygofer short, approximately quadrangular, with bifurcate apical lobe and microsetae on apex and ventral margin (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA48273FED5F81C59A7D0AA" box="[335,468,1988,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">
Figs 17 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA48273FE3DF81C59C6D0AB" bold="true" box="[423,437,1988,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">–</emphasis>
18
</figureCitation>
). Style with strong basal curvature, with thin apex ventrally curved, lateral margins smooth, microsetae only on apical portion (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA58272FD0BFF4F5B65D7C6" box="[657,790,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
Figs 20 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FD73FF4F5A84D7C6" bold="true" box="[745,759,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">–</emphasis>
21
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus enlarged, with two pairs of apical long and slender processes (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA58272FEF3FF64599FD7A2" box="[361,492,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
Figs 22 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FE27FF6459B8D7A3" bold="true" box="[445,459,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">–</emphasis>
24
</figureCitation>
). Anal tube with pair of short processes with rounded apices (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA58272FB05FF645D53D7A2" box="[1183,1312,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
Figs 17 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FB69FF645D72D7A3" bold="true" box="[1267,1281,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">–</emphasis>
18
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF3C6678FFA58272FF0DFA2C5CC2D111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="414" targetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F0FFA58272FF0DFA2C5CC2D111" blockId="5.[151,1436,1524,1639]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FF0DFA2C5926D17C" bold="true" box="[151,341,1524,1547]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">FIGURES 13–24.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C434D73FFA58272FEC6FA2D5A40D17D" authority="Ale-Rocha, 2017" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2017" box="[348,563,1525,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xiqilliba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sakakibarai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FEC6FA2D5A40D17D" box="[348,563,1525,1547]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">Xiqilliba sakakibarai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2045799FFA58272FDA1FA2D5AFFD17C" box="[571,652,1525,1546]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FDA1FA2D5AFFD17C" bold="true" box="[571,652,1525,1546]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male holotype: 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FCA1FA2D5B27D17C" bold="true" box="[827,852,1525,1546]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">13</emphasis>
, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FAA5FA2D5D2BD17C" bold="true" box="[1343,1368,1525,1546]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">14</emphasis>
, head, frontal view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FEBCF9CC594CD15F" bold="true" box="[294,319,1556,1577]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">15</emphasis>
, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FCA6F9CC5B26D15F" bold="true" box="[828,853,1556,1577]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">16</emphasis>
, forewing; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FC4BF9CC5B99D15F" bold="true" box="[977,1002,1556,1577]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">17</emphasis>
, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FAE6F9CC5DE6D15F" bold="true" box="[1404,1429,1556,1577]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">18</emphasis>
, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FD96F9EA5A56D131" bold="true" box="[524,549,1586,1607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">19</emphasis>
, subgenital plates, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FCEEF9EA5BFED131" bold="true" box="[884,909,1586,1607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">20</emphasis>
, style, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FBC6F9EA5C06D131" bold="true" box="[1116,1141,1586,1607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">21</emphasis>
, connective and style, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FF4FF989589DD110" bold="true" box="[213,238,1617,1638]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">22</emphasis>
, aedeagus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FE73F9895A7BD110" bold="true" box="[489,520,1617,1638]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">23,</emphasis>
apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FCD6F9895B16D110" bold="true" box="[844,869,1617,1638]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">24</emphasis>
, apex of aedeagus, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C359657BFFA58271FF5DF9565AC2D129" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="415" pageId="5" pageNumber="414" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F0FFA58272FF5DF95659FCD065" blockId="5.[151,1437,1678,2027]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FF5DF95659BBD1D1" bold="true" box="[199,456,1678,1703]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus id="54F88852FFA58272FD8FF9565A0FD1D1" box="[533,636,1678,1703]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">holotype</typeStatus>
: total length 5.86; crown median length 0.48; transocular width 1.36; interocular width 0.68; frons basal width 0.52; frons length 0.96; pronotum median length 0.56; width between humeri 1.60; mesonotum median length 0.92; mesonotum maximum width 1.00; forewing length 4.54; forewing maximum width 1.12.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F0FFA58271FF5DF8C659BDD649" blockId="5.[151,1437,1678,2027]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="415" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FF5DF8C6591CD041" bold="true" box="[199,367,1822,1847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">General color.</emphasis>
Pale-yellow with dark-brown markings (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA58272FCA0F8C65BCED041" box="[826,957,1822,1847]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,825,1416]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[159,1428,825,1416]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Male holotype, dorsal and lateral view: 25 – 26, Xiqilliba bellator; 27 – 28, Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847942/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">
Figs 27 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA58272FC15F8C65BEED041" bold="true" box="[911,925,1822,1847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="414">–</emphasis>
28
</figureCitation>
). Head in anterior view yellow; frons paleyellow, with median round dark-brown mark at base, and antennal ledges spotted with light-brown; genae, maxillary plates and lora whitish to pale-yellow, lora with apical half dark-brown. Crown whitish; with wide longitudinal median stripe light-brown in central portion and dark-brown more laterad, narrowed, and basally prolonged laterad, broader in apical half. Proepimeron and proepisternum whitish to pale-yellow; pronotum whitish with lateral and posterior margins pale-yellow and wide longitudinal brown stripe medially; pleura and ventral of thorax whitish, spotted with dark-brown; mesonotum yellowish to light-brown with pair of dark-brown marks close to lateral angles and two narrow longitudinal parallel dark-brown stripes extending close to apex. Forewing hyaline, infuscated with brown, with yellowish veins, and large whitish mark at base that extends along costal margin to preapical portion. Hind wing brown with veins of same color. Legs pale-yellow to light-brown with yellow to brown setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F0FFA68271FF5DFE945C94D463" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FF5DFE94592AD613" bold="true" box="[199,345,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Description.</emphasis>
Structural characters as in generic description, except male genitalia: in lateral view, pygofer short, approximately quadrangular but abruptly narrowed at apical third, with bifurcate apical lobe and microsetae on apex and ventral margin (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FE47FE4C5A13D6DA" box="[477,608,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
Figs 17 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FDA9FE4C5A32D6DB" bold="true" box="[563,577,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">–</emphasis>
18
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates approximately triangular, enlarged basally, narrowing towards apex; fused in basal half, with central cleft, reaching median third; apices acutely rounded, microsetae on outer margins from apical third and at apex; plates longer than pygofer and approximately twice longer than basal width (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FF7DFE275940D56E" box="[231,307,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Fig.19</figureCitation>
). Style extremely long and slender, with strong basal curvature, with thin apex ventrally curved, and lateral margins smooth, microsetae only in apical portion (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FCABFDFC5BC0D54A" box="[817,947,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
Figs 20 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FC1DFDFC5BE6D54B" bold="true" box="[903,917,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">–</emphasis>
21
</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped, approximately one fourth length of style, stalk enlarged and articulated to base of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FC67FD9F5C26D516" box="[1021,1109,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus, in lateral view, enlarged, except at apex; base with long and thick apodeme; shaft approximately straight, with dorsal curvature only in median and apical fourths; ventral margin flat, without teeth; apex rounded, with two pairs of long and slender apical processes, inner one thin with pointed apex, outer one thickened, apical half thicker than basal half, with inner margin medially serrate, apex rounded, gonopore apical (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FC2EFD0F5C49D586" box="[948,1082,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
Figs 22 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FB96FD0F5C69D586" bold="true" box="[1036,1050,727,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">–</emphasis>
24
</figureCitation>
). Anal tube with pair of short processes not crossing inside genital capsule, with rounded apices (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FC12FD245C7AD462" box="[904,1033,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
Figs 17 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FC46FD245B99D463" bold="true" box="[988,1002,764,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">–</emphasis>
18
</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
