<subSubSection id="C359657BFFA68271FF5DF9B35CF7D1BA" pageId="6" pageNumber="415" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F0FFA68271FF5DF9B35CF7D1BA" blockId="6.[151,1436,1535,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FF5DF9B359C1D1F2" bold="true" box="[199,434,1643,1668]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
<typeStatus id="54F88852FFA68271FF5DF9B35947D1F2" box="[199,308,1643,1668]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Holotype</typeStatus>
condition.
</emphasis>
Right antenna missing; left with apical half of flagellum missing. Thorax ventrally glued to entomological triangle. Fore legs in perfect state, but glued to entomological triangle; median legs, hind legs and wings in perfect state of conservation, wings with apices bent inside. Abdomen dissected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C359657BFFA68271FF5DF90F5A26D09A" pageId="6" pageNumber="415" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F0FFA68271FF5DF90F5CEFD04E" blockId="6.[151,1436,1535,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FF5DF90F593DD186" bold="true" box="[199,334,1751,1776]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is a tribute to the great researcher and senior professor Dr. Albino Morimasa Sakakibara, due to his contributions to the knowledge of neotropical Auchenorrhyncha, especially 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D73FFA68271FB61F9235DEBD062" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[1275,1432,1787,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Membracidae</taxonomicName>
, and also for contributing for the professional formation of many Brazilian hemipterologists.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F0FFA68271FF5DF89B5A26D09A" blockId="6.[151,1436,1535,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FF5DF89B5962D02A" bold="true" box="[199,273,1859,1884]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C434D73FFA68271FE82F89B5A75D02A" authority="Ale-Rocha, 2017" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2017" box="[280,518,1859,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xiqilliba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sakakibarai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FE82F89B5A75D02A" box="[280,518,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Xiqilliba sakakibarai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2045799FFA68271FD94F89B5A1AD02A" box="[526,617,1859,1884]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FD94F89B5A1AD02A" bold="true" box="[526,617,1859,1884]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D73FFA68271FD64F89B5C6DD02D" authority="Kramer" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1964" box="[766,1054,1859,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xiqilliba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellator">
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FD64F89B5BB2D02A" box="[766,961,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Xiqilliba bellator</emphasis>
Kramer
</taxonomicName>
regarding the color pattern of the crown, pronotum, mesonotum, and forewings (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FD5BF8BF5B34D0F6" box="[705,839,1895,1920]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Figs 13–16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FCC3F8BF5BD0D009" box="[857,931,1895,1919]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1437,1460]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,825,1416]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[159,1428,825,1416]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Male holotype, dorsal and lateral view: 25 – 26, Xiqilliba bellator; 27 – 28, Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847942/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">27–28</figureCitation>
), and also by the shape and length of the subgenital plates (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FEFCF85359C9D0D2" box="[358,442,1931,1956]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) and connective (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FD13F8535AACD0D2" box="[649,735,1931,1956]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). It differs mainly by the shape of the pygofer and anal tube processes (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FE8BF87759E1D0B1" box="[273,402,1967,1992]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
Figs 17 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FEFFF8775900D0BE" bold="true" box="[357,371,1967,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">–</emphasis>
18
</figureCitation>
); the presence of strong curvature at the base of the style (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FB81F8775CEED0B1" box="[1051,1181,1967,1992]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
Figs 20 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FBEAF8775C0DD0BE" bold="true" box="[1136,1150,1967,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">–</emphasis>
21
</figureCitation>
); and by the shape and processes of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13782A75FFA68271FE5CF80B5A3AD09A" box="[454,585,2003,2028]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1524,1547]" captionTargetBox="[205,1392,277,1495]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[181,1405,265,1503]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Xiqilliba sakakibarai sp. nov., male holotype: 13, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 14, head, frontal view; 15, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 16, forewing; 17, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 18, pygofer and anal tube, ventral view; 19, subgenital plates, ventral view; 20, style, lateral view; 21, connective and style, dorsal view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 24, apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847940/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">
Figs 22 
<emphasis id="B937EAE2FFA68271FD81F80B5A5AD09A" bold="true" box="[539,553,2003,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="415">–</emphasis>
24
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
